4
00:01:27,298 --> 00:01:28,838
EPISODE 3

5
00:01:34,308 --> 00:01:37,348
Hey, have you lost your mind?
What do you mean, his fiancée?

6
00:01:38,268 --> 00:01:39,938
That punk has amnesia.

7
00:01:40,398 --> 00:01:43,018
But still. This is totally insane.

8
00:01:43,148 --> 00:01:44,148
They'll find out soon…

9
00:01:48,858 --> 00:01:51,368
Did you really try
to kill Mr. Noh Manners?

10
00:01:52,528 --> 00:01:53,788
It sounds suspicious.

11
00:01:53,868 --> 00:01:55,118
Otherwise, why did you go there?

12
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:56,788
Why did you go there with a claw hammer?

13
00:02:02,918 --> 00:02:05,208
You're right. I went there to kill him.

14
00:02:11,508 --> 00:02:13,508
VIP WARD

15
00:02:30,908 --> 00:02:32,238
You can't enter his room.

16
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:34,328
Ms. Lee Sina is our prime suspect…

17
00:02:40,538 --> 00:02:43,748
What is it?
The vehicle inspection results came out?

18
00:02:45,128 --> 00:02:46,418
What about the bloodstains?

19
00:02:47,838 --> 00:02:50,168
None. It wasn't a collision with a person?

20
00:02:52,638 --> 00:02:53,638
Okay, got it.

21
00:02:56,598 --> 00:02:59,138
He said no, right?
Sina didn't hit him, right?

22
00:02:59,228 --> 00:03:00,478
We don't know yet.

23
00:03:01,058 --> 00:03:03,978
We just don't have conclusive evidence,
but all circumstantial evidence

24
00:03:04,608 --> 00:03:06,688
points to Ms. Lee Sina.

25
00:03:07,358 --> 00:03:10,068
Hence, Ms. Lee Sina is
still our prime suspect.

26
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,318
I'm telling you, she didn't hit him!

27
00:03:12,408 --> 00:03:15,408
She's too nice to even harm a fly.

28
00:03:15,488 --> 00:03:17,288
-You're her lawyer.
-I'm not a lawyer.

29
00:03:19,288 --> 00:03:20,118
Didn't you say

30
00:03:20,908 --> 00:03:22,958
that you're representing Ms. Lee Sina?

31
00:03:24,248 --> 00:03:27,918
I said that because
I'm a friend who lives with her.

32
00:03:29,088 --> 00:03:30,128
I'm…

33
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:32,758
an actress.

34
00:03:33,508 --> 00:03:37,638
I'm a stage actress
who works part-time at a lawyer's office.

35
00:03:39,678 --> 00:03:42,728
If you have any free time,
please come watch a play

36
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:44,438
at Daehangno.

37
00:03:45,648 --> 00:03:48,318
Here you go. One more.

38
00:03:48,398 --> 00:03:50,108
Okay, thank you.

39
00:03:52,068 --> 00:03:53,358
Please make sure to come.

40
00:04:14,178 --> 00:04:15,048
Mr. Noh Gojin?

41
00:04:20,768 --> 00:04:21,928
How are you doing?

42
00:04:26,058 --> 00:04:27,558
You've been calling me that

43
00:04:28,108 --> 00:04:29,728
from the moment I woke up.

44
00:04:31,978 --> 00:04:33,858
Is that my name?

45
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:37,158
Noh Gojin?

46
00:04:37,738 --> 00:04:38,988
Yes, that's right.

47
00:04:41,578 --> 00:04:43,658
Is there anything you can remember?

48
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:48,078
No.

49
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:51,998
That name sounds so unfamiliar.

50
00:04:53,798 --> 00:04:54,798
Noh Gojin.

51
00:04:56,468 --> 00:04:57,508
What about my age?

52
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:01,968
How old am I?

53
00:05:02,638 --> 00:05:05,138
You're 35 years old by Korean age.

54
00:05:05,978 --> 00:05:07,188
I'm 35?

55
00:05:09,858 --> 00:05:10,858
Then,

56
00:05:12,068 --> 00:05:13,858
why did I end up here?

57
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:16,648
You came to the hospital
after a car accident.

58
00:05:17,318 --> 00:05:18,448
A car accident…

59
00:05:21,078 --> 00:05:22,078
So that's why

60
00:05:22,868 --> 00:05:24,118
my leg is like this.

61
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:30,288
May I ask you something?

62
00:05:31,788 --> 00:05:33,588
I have a pretty serious injury on my leg.

63
00:05:34,508 --> 00:05:36,298
Then why can't I
even remember my own name?

64
00:05:37,468 --> 00:05:39,258
We'll do another brain scan,

65
00:05:40,008 --> 00:05:41,138
but I believe

66
00:05:41,218 --> 00:05:44,518
that you were traumatized
during the surgery.

67
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,598
Traumatized?

68
00:05:46,678 --> 00:05:50,858
Because you have a unique constitution,
you cannot be anesthetized.

69
00:05:51,688 --> 00:05:53,978
You were not anesthetized completely,

70
00:05:54,068 --> 00:05:56,108
so you were aware of the whole surgery.

71
00:05:56,528 --> 00:05:59,408
It's a side effect caused by stress.

72
00:05:59,908 --> 00:06:01,198
It's a type of trauma.

73
00:06:05,078 --> 00:06:06,078
Does that mean…

74
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,328
that I'll have to keep…

75
00:06:10,788 --> 00:06:13,248
living like this
without even knowing who I am?

76
00:06:13,338 --> 00:06:17,378
It's highly probable
that your amnesia is temporary.

77
00:06:18,168 --> 00:06:19,468
Based on previous cases,

78
00:06:20,048 --> 00:06:24,508
patients who've lost their memories
due to side effects of anesthesia like you

79
00:06:24,598 --> 00:06:26,138
mostly got their memories back

80
00:06:26,808 --> 00:06:28,768
even though their recovery time
may have varied.

81
00:06:30,558 --> 00:06:31,648
Is that really the case?

82
00:06:32,268 --> 00:06:33,728
They really got their memories back?

83
00:06:33,808 --> 00:06:34,978
Yes.

84
00:06:37,528 --> 00:06:39,898
I know you must feel very anxious,

85
00:06:40,318 --> 00:06:43,908
but the best thing you can do now
is to give yourself some time

86
00:06:44,328 --> 00:06:45,788
and keep making efforts.

87
00:06:50,408 --> 00:06:53,708
Do you remember her by any chance?

88
00:07:13,268 --> 00:07:14,728
Please take a closer look.

89
00:07:20,238 --> 00:07:21,238
Remember it.

90
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:23,908
Just remember the fact
that you got slapped by me at least.

91
00:07:24,368 --> 00:07:26,238
Then I'll stop here.

92
00:07:30,788 --> 00:07:31,828
No, I don't.

93
00:07:35,128 --> 00:07:37,378
No. You have to remember me.

94
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,128
I've never seen her before.

95
00:07:42,798 --> 00:07:43,928
She's someone

96
00:07:44,928 --> 00:07:47,758
who is the closest to you.

97
00:07:50,638 --> 00:07:54,058
Closest to me?

98
00:07:56,688 --> 00:07:57,648
Who is she?

99
00:07:58,858 --> 00:07:59,898
She is…

100
00:08:01,778 --> 00:08:02,858
your fiancée.

101
00:08:03,568 --> 00:08:06,528
My… fiancée?

102
00:08:08,118 --> 00:08:09,078
Yes.

103
00:08:09,738 --> 00:08:10,748
It's me.

104
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:13,538
Your fiancée.

105
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,378
I won't die with things like this.

106
00:08:33,478 --> 00:08:35,848
How is he? Did he recognize Sina…

107
00:08:36,438 --> 00:08:38,108
I mean, his fiancée?

108
00:08:41,778 --> 00:08:42,738
He really has amnesia.

109
00:08:43,608 --> 00:08:46,858
Mr. Noh Gojin doesn't even remember
his own name right now.

110
00:08:46,948 --> 00:08:48,068
Not even his own name?

111
00:08:48,158 --> 00:08:49,578
No, he doesn't.

112
00:08:50,738 --> 00:08:51,868
That's insane.

113
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,118
But perhaps,

114
00:08:53,828 --> 00:08:57,038
their love can help him heal.

115
00:08:57,628 --> 00:08:58,538
Love?

116
00:09:00,378 --> 00:09:01,628
That should be the case, right?

117
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,668
Their love can help him heal, right?

118
00:09:05,508 --> 00:09:08,298
Because love is so great.

119
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:10,388
-So great.
-All right!

120
00:09:10,468 --> 00:09:11,928
Love is so great!

121
00:09:12,348 --> 00:09:14,888
Doctor, I love you!

122
00:09:17,808 --> 00:09:19,058
So you're…

123
00:09:19,648 --> 00:09:20,978
my fiancée?

124
00:09:21,898 --> 00:09:22,728
Yes.

125
00:09:35,368 --> 00:09:36,578
What's wrong?

126
00:09:36,658 --> 00:09:37,828
My head…

127
00:09:38,868 --> 00:09:39,788
My head hurts so much.

128
00:09:40,498 --> 00:09:41,538
Should I call the doctor?

129
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:42,998
I remember…

130
00:09:51,098 --> 00:09:52,928
You remember…

131
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:55,308
something?

132
00:09:58,098 --> 00:09:58,938
No.

133
00:10:00,598 --> 00:10:01,688
I remember nothing.

134
00:10:06,608 --> 00:10:07,778
I'm tired.

135
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,868
Maybe I thought too hard.

136
00:10:12,318 --> 00:10:13,698
I want to rest.

137
00:10:13,778 --> 00:10:16,368
Right, don't force yourself too hard
to remember things.

138
00:10:16,448 --> 00:10:19,418
The doctor also said that
remaining calm is best for you.

139
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:22,748
I'll be outside. Please rest well.

140
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:26,958
Wait.

141
00:10:33,928 --> 00:10:35,138
Yes?

142
00:10:36,428 --> 00:10:37,478
Thank you.

143
00:10:38,728 --> 00:10:41,768
I heard that I have no family.

144
00:10:44,188 --> 00:10:45,568
I'm so relieved

145
00:10:46,568 --> 00:10:47,898
that I'm not alone.

146
00:11:12,218 --> 00:11:14,048
What's wrong? Are you okay?

147
00:11:15,888 --> 00:11:16,968
Okhee.

148
00:11:17,388 --> 00:11:18,678
What? What happened?

149
00:11:20,058 --> 00:11:21,808
He really must be dying.

150
00:11:21,888 --> 00:11:23,018
What?

151
00:11:23,478 --> 00:11:25,398
What the heck are you talking about?

152
00:11:27,188 --> 00:11:28,568
Noh Gojin said…

153
00:11:32,318 --> 00:11:33,488
Noh Gojin said…

154
00:11:33,908 --> 00:11:36,278
Yeah, what did Mr. Noh Manners say?

155
00:11:38,158 --> 00:11:38,988
"thank you."

156
00:11:39,078 --> 00:11:40,118
What?

157
00:11:40,198 --> 00:11:42,118
He thanked me.

158
00:11:44,288 --> 00:11:45,378
How is this possible?

159
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:48,958
That's insane.
He really did lose his mind.

160
00:11:49,048 --> 00:11:51,758
My goodness. This is crazy.

161
00:11:51,838 --> 00:11:53,508
What are the odds of this happening?

162
00:11:53,588 --> 00:11:54,638
Unbelievable.

163
00:11:57,758 --> 00:11:59,928
He's the one who mistreated me.
How can he be at peace?

164
00:12:03,018 --> 00:12:04,308
He can't just forget.

165
00:12:06,188 --> 00:12:09,778
He can't just forget everything
and thank me with an angelic face.

166
00:12:10,728 --> 00:12:11,738
I…

167
00:12:14,408 --> 00:12:17,238
What did I do so wrong?

168
00:12:17,318 --> 00:12:18,738
I really worked hard all my life.

169
00:12:18,828 --> 00:12:21,158
There wasn't a moment
in my life when I didn't work hard.

170
00:12:21,248 --> 00:12:23,748
I've never done
anything bad in my whole life!

171
00:12:23,828 --> 00:12:25,368
Why is this happening to me?

172
00:12:25,458 --> 00:12:27,038
What did I do so wrong?

173
00:12:27,128 --> 00:12:29,298
Why? Why do I have to die?

174
00:12:33,298 --> 00:12:35,338
Why would you die because of this?

175
00:12:39,888 --> 00:12:41,348
Fine. Cry.

176
00:12:42,138 --> 00:12:44,518
You'll feel better after crying.

177
00:12:47,228 --> 00:12:48,608
By the way,

178
00:12:48,688 --> 00:12:49,858
it's not true, right?

179
00:12:52,738 --> 00:12:53,898
What you said earlier.

180
00:12:54,818 --> 00:12:55,948
You went there to kill him.

181
00:12:57,908 --> 00:12:58,818
You were joking, right?

182
00:13:01,078 --> 00:13:02,698
I know you so well.

183
00:13:02,828 --> 00:13:05,918
Sina, you're so timid.
You'd never dare kill anyone.

184
00:13:06,418 --> 00:13:08,378
Gosh, this is making me so angry.

185
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:10,838
The police are suspecting you
to be the hit-and-run driver,

186
00:13:11,088 --> 00:13:12,878
and Mr. Noh Manners has lost his mind.

187
00:13:13,378 --> 00:13:15,378
What if you get blamed for everything?

188
00:13:16,218 --> 00:13:17,048
Let's do something.

189
00:13:17,638 --> 00:13:20,298
-I'll call my boss--
-Don't.

190
00:13:20,888 --> 00:13:22,348
I didn't do anything wrong.

191
00:13:23,968 --> 00:13:25,558
I swear on my father's life.

192
00:13:27,138 --> 00:13:28,898
Then please go confess now.

193
00:13:28,978 --> 00:13:30,938
-Tell the police that you lied about--
-No.

194
00:13:32,018 --> 00:13:34,228
-I don't want to.
-Why not?

195
00:13:37,448 --> 00:13:38,488
I'm going to get revenge.

196
00:13:39,738 --> 00:13:40,908
Revenge?

197
00:13:41,528 --> 00:13:42,698
I won't…

198
00:13:43,288 --> 00:13:44,908
put up with him anymore.

199
00:13:46,288 --> 00:13:47,868
I'm not just going to die like a fool.

200
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:50,958
Noh Gojin, that scumbag!

201
00:13:53,498 --> 00:13:54,918
I'm going to destroy him.

202
00:14:03,178 --> 00:14:04,348
We're here, ma'am.

203
00:14:04,888 --> 00:14:06,558
The automatic stop has been activated.

204
00:14:06,638 --> 00:14:07,638
Ma'am.

205
00:14:08,478 --> 00:14:09,438
Ma'am?

206
00:14:11,608 --> 00:14:12,688
We're here.

207
00:14:13,398 --> 00:14:15,648
Oh… Right.

208
00:14:18,448 --> 00:14:19,448
Ma'am.

209
00:14:20,028 --> 00:14:21,698
Aren't you taking this?

210
00:14:36,628 --> 00:14:38,718
Hello? I'm at the hospital.

211
00:14:39,838 --> 00:14:41,638
I came to visit
the president of the school.

212
00:14:42,678 --> 00:14:44,468
Okay. I'll call you on the way.

213
00:14:44,968 --> 00:14:45,968
Okay. Bye.

214
00:15:03,908 --> 00:15:06,408
Oh, right. Did you hear?

215
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:07,488
What?

216
00:15:07,788 --> 00:15:10,078
Noh Gojin is hospitalized here.

217
00:15:10,708 --> 00:15:11,708
Noh Gojin?

218
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:14,328
That top instructor Noh Gojin?

219
00:15:14,418 --> 00:15:16,418
That's right. He's at the VIP Ward.

220
00:15:16,998 --> 00:15:18,008
That's crazy.

221
00:15:18,168 --> 00:15:21,128
Thanks to Mr. Noh's lectures,
I placed at the top level for math.

222
00:15:21,378 --> 00:15:23,178
-Seriously?
-That's amazing.

223
00:15:58,628 --> 00:15:59,628
Hi.

224
00:16:01,128 --> 00:16:02,418
How have you been?

225
00:16:05,718 --> 00:16:07,048
It's been so long.

226
00:16:17,898 --> 00:16:19,728
How much were you hurt?

227
00:16:21,278 --> 00:16:22,278
Who…

228
00:16:23,568 --> 00:16:24,488
are you?

229
00:16:27,988 --> 00:16:29,278
Do you know me?

230
00:17:20,168 --> 00:17:22,838
You want me to do this?

231
00:17:22,918 --> 00:17:23,918
Yes.

232
00:17:30,678 --> 00:17:33,888
Don't be frustrated and do it slowly
even if you can't do it well…

233
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:21,808
The Ramanujan Summation states
that if you add

234
00:18:22,398 --> 00:18:23,768
all the natural numbers,

235
00:18:24,898 --> 00:18:26,438
it'll equal to -1/12, a negative number.

236
00:18:29,318 --> 00:18:31,408
The aviation security regulations
announcement.

237
00:18:31,488 --> 00:18:33,698
The quantity of liquids and gels

238
00:18:34,408 --> 00:18:38,328
you can carry onboard
international flights is restricted…

239
00:18:39,038 --> 00:18:41,208
Mr. Oh, your car isn't here, right?

240
00:18:41,288 --> 00:18:43,588
I'll drive you home.

241
00:18:43,668 --> 00:18:45,128
Thank you, but it's okay.

242
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,008
I have to go to the office
for my cell phone.

243
00:18:47,088 --> 00:18:50,678
It might've exploded
because of the continued missed calls.

244
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:52,428
My car is at the office too.

245
00:18:52,758 --> 00:18:53,848
I'll drive you there--

246
00:18:53,928 --> 00:18:55,718
Gosh, it's okay.

247
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:59,228
You worked hard.
Please rest well and see you at work.

248
00:19:08,818 --> 00:19:10,198
You're really going to do it?

249
00:19:13,158 --> 00:19:15,618
You really resent
Mr. Noh Manners, don't you?

250
00:19:17,828 --> 00:19:19,578
Fine. Go for it.

251
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:20,868
Get your revenge.

252
00:19:21,828 --> 00:19:27,128
It's unbelievable that he has amnesia.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

253
00:19:28,008 --> 00:19:29,798
Do it. Get revenge.

254
00:19:32,008 --> 00:19:34,008
It's your engagement ring,

255
00:19:34,088 --> 00:19:37,178
You need the perfect prop
if you're to be his fiancée.

256
00:19:37,258 --> 00:19:38,968
Wait.

257
00:19:39,058 --> 00:19:42,638
But what if Mr. Noh Manners
recovers his memories soon?

258
00:19:42,728 --> 00:19:45,268
It doesn't matter
even if he does tomorrow.

259
00:19:45,938 --> 00:19:49,188
I'm going to die anyway, so who cares?

260
00:19:50,108 --> 00:19:53,778
You're right. We'll all die anyway.

261
00:19:53,858 --> 00:19:55,118
You have nothing to lose.

262
00:19:55,198 --> 00:19:58,788
Lee Sina, you're so cool.
You should've been like this sooner.

263
00:19:58,868 --> 00:20:02,958
I know.
Why did I put up with it like a fool?

264
00:20:03,038 --> 00:20:05,418
Hey, take this chance
and get back at him for everything.

265
00:20:05,498 --> 00:20:07,288
Hit him in the head,

266
00:20:07,378 --> 00:20:08,668
and spit in his water.

267
00:20:08,748 --> 00:20:10,378
Mix in a laxative in his food too.

268
00:20:10,668 --> 00:20:13,048
Do everything you want. Here you go.

269
00:20:27,518 --> 00:20:31,688
Let me show you what true acting means.

270
00:20:31,778 --> 00:20:34,528
This is how you can be more real
than his actual fiancée

271
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:37,318
by pouring your blood, sweat,
and tears into acting.

272
00:20:37,408 --> 00:20:41,198
I'll give you
a special crash course in acting.

273
00:21:00,468 --> 00:21:01,388
Be careful.

274
00:21:14,528 --> 00:21:15,528
Are you comfortable?

275
00:21:48,558 --> 00:21:49,558
I'm sorry.

276
00:21:50,938 --> 00:21:52,398
