291
00:23:19,528 --> 00:23:20,488
Honey?

292
00:23:20,568 --> 00:23:23,818
Honey, eat lots and die…

293
00:23:27,288 --> 00:23:30,958
Work hard to death
to recover your memories, okay?

294
00:23:31,538 --> 00:23:32,368
Thank you.

295
00:23:52,268 --> 00:23:53,098
How is it?

296
00:23:53,978 --> 00:23:55,058
It tastes good.

297
00:23:55,688 --> 00:23:59,028
Doesn't it? This isn't ordinary water.

298
00:23:59,318 --> 00:24:02,108
It's much better
than imported mineral water,

299
00:24:02,198 --> 00:24:04,738
so I really went out of my way
to get it for you, honey.

300
00:24:04,818 --> 00:24:06,948
What kind of water is it?

301
00:24:15,828 --> 00:24:16,918
ONION EXTRACT

302
00:24:21,088 --> 00:24:22,508
Ta-da!

303
00:24:23,218 --> 00:24:24,678
What's all this?

304
00:24:24,758 --> 00:24:26,468
You love onions so much, honey.

305
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:28,218
Don't they look so delicious?

306
00:24:28,308 --> 00:24:32,138
I had to go through all sorts of trouble
to get these specially made from a hotel.

307
00:24:32,228 --> 00:24:33,558
You have to eat everything, okay?

308
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:35,688
Did I like onions--

309
00:24:38,188 --> 00:24:40,358
Try it first. You'll really love it.

310
00:24:43,528 --> 00:24:44,818
Chew well. Come on.

311
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:51,118
Isn't it so delicious?

312
00:24:52,288 --> 00:24:56,288
Honey, you also love onion rings.
Try these.

313
00:24:57,128 --> 00:24:59,668
You really love raw onion too.
You always got an extra serving.

314
00:24:59,748 --> 00:25:02,798
Oh, are you thirsty?
You should drink some onion extract.

315
00:25:02,878 --> 00:25:04,968
Here you go. Onion extract juice.

316
00:25:05,048 --> 00:25:07,048
No, it's okay. It's okay!

317
00:25:08,258 --> 00:25:10,888
Come on. Drink up.

318
00:25:14,428 --> 00:25:16,688
I really don't want to go.

319
00:25:17,268 --> 00:25:19,018
My stomach feels so awful.

320
00:25:19,108 --> 00:25:20,688
That's why you should get some fresh air.

321
00:25:20,768 --> 00:25:22,938
All you've done is lie down and eat.

322
00:25:23,648 --> 00:25:24,648
Oh, right!

323
00:25:25,108 --> 00:25:26,948
I forgot to put sunscreen on you.

324
00:25:27,608 --> 00:25:29,118
You can't get sunburned.

325
00:25:41,708 --> 00:25:43,168
Here you go.

326
00:25:46,048 --> 00:25:48,258
You can't get sunburned, honey.

327
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:51,848
I have to apply it very thoroughly.

328
00:26:02,568 --> 00:26:04,028
Is that a facial mask?

329
00:26:11,028 --> 00:26:13,948
Now that I'm outside, it feels very nice.

330
00:26:17,828 --> 00:26:19,538
-Hello.
-Mr. Oh.

331
00:26:20,128 --> 00:26:21,418
You're back a week early.

332
00:26:21,498 --> 00:26:23,588
The meeting went well,
so I came back early.

333
00:26:23,668 --> 00:26:24,628
I see.

334
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:26,508
To celebrate that…

335
00:26:30,678 --> 00:26:34,058
-I got you a souvenir.
-You really didn't have to. Thank you.

336
00:26:34,138 --> 00:26:36,308
-Thank you for your hard work.
-Yes, sir.

337
00:26:42,558 --> 00:26:45,148
My goodness.
You're back to the office, Mr. Oh!

338
00:26:45,228 --> 00:26:46,318
Hello, it's been a while.

339
00:26:46,398 --> 00:26:49,608
Goodness. How was your business trip?

340
00:26:49,698 --> 00:26:51,818
It was great. Thank you for asking.

341
00:26:52,408 --> 00:26:54,988
You were gone only for a few days,

342
00:26:55,238 --> 00:26:56,748
but it felt like years to me.

343
00:26:56,998 --> 00:26:58,248
Goodness.

344
00:26:58,908 --> 00:27:03,668
The office feels so gloomy without you.

345
00:27:04,958 --> 00:27:06,208
I'm serious.

346
00:27:06,708 --> 00:27:09,508
I really missed you.

347
00:27:10,008 --> 00:27:13,338
I really missed you too, Ms. Gong.

348
00:27:13,428 --> 00:27:16,058
Oh, right. Since I missed you…

349
00:27:18,428 --> 00:27:19,428
Ta-da.

350
00:27:20,848 --> 00:27:23,228
My goodness. What's this?

351
00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:25,518
It's nothing big. Just a souvenir.

352
00:27:26,398 --> 00:27:27,318
You shouldn't have.

353
00:27:27,398 --> 00:27:28,778
Thank you.

354
00:27:28,858 --> 00:27:30,278
-Thank you.
-My pleasure.

355
00:27:30,358 --> 00:27:31,908
Well then, I'll get going.

356
00:27:31,988 --> 00:27:33,238
Okay. Thank you.

357
00:27:33,318 --> 00:27:34,528
-Thank you.
-Bye.

358
00:27:36,948 --> 00:27:38,948
GOTOP EDUCATION

359
00:27:44,958 --> 00:27:46,918
CALLS

360
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:48,958
I had so many missed calls. Jeez.

361
00:27:52,628 --> 00:27:53,638
Hello?

362
00:27:54,508 --> 00:27:57,758
Yes, this is Oh Segi, Deputy CEO
of Gotop Education. Who's this?

363
00:27:59,348 --> 00:28:00,478
Police?

364
00:28:02,058 --> 00:28:03,388
How may I help you?

365
00:28:05,188 --> 00:28:08,688
What did you say?
Mr. Noh got hit by a car?

366
00:29:17,298 --> 00:29:18,508
Ms. Ma.

367
00:29:27,438 --> 00:29:28,608
Since that's the case…

368
00:29:29,648 --> 00:29:30,858
What's going on?

369
00:29:31,318 --> 00:29:33,438
Mr. Noh Manners…

370
00:29:33,528 --> 00:29:37,408
What? Tell us the details… Jeez.

371
00:29:40,238 --> 00:29:42,038
Hey! Did you hear…

372
00:29:42,118 --> 00:29:44,078
-Seriously? No way.
-Let's go.

373
00:29:59,718 --> 00:30:02,808
-Noh Gojin got hit by a car!
-Noh Gojin got hit by a car!

374
00:30:14,028 --> 00:30:15,108
NOH GOJIN

375
00:30:15,188 --> 00:30:16,438
CEO NOH GOJIN WITH AN IQ OF 190

376
00:30:19,448 --> 00:30:20,618
KOREA'S NO. 1 ONLINE CLASS

377
00:30:22,618 --> 00:30:25,368
Korea's No. 1 online class,
Gotop Education.

378
00:30:25,948 --> 00:30:28,458
Choose… now.

379
00:30:32,088 --> 00:30:33,128
Now I get it.

380
00:30:33,998 --> 00:30:37,838
I'm a very popular, top instructor,

381
00:30:37,918 --> 00:30:40,388
who is the CEO of Gotop Education, right?

382
00:30:42,388 --> 00:30:43,848
Yes, you finally realized.

383
00:30:44,848 --> 00:30:46,558
I never imagined

384
00:30:47,388 --> 00:30:50,598
I was a person who taught others.

385
00:30:51,978 --> 00:30:52,938
I've done…

386
00:30:54,438 --> 00:30:56,028
such a good job with my life.

387
00:31:01,658 --> 00:31:04,238
Sure, you've done a good job

388
00:31:04,408 --> 00:31:06,118
making other people suffer.

389
00:31:09,828 --> 00:31:12,958
Then, how did we meet?

390
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:14,708
At work, of course.

391
00:31:14,788 --> 00:31:15,998
The CEO and his secretary.

392
00:31:16,088 --> 00:31:19,048
Oh, I see. You're my secretary.

393
00:31:19,548 --> 00:31:24,008
Then everyone at work should know
that we're engaged, right?

394
00:31:25,678 --> 00:31:27,098
-No.
-Why not?

395
00:31:27,678 --> 00:31:29,518
Because…

396
00:31:30,598 --> 00:31:31,978
we dated each other secretly

397
00:31:32,058 --> 00:31:34,148
and exchanged vows on our own.

398
00:31:34,228 --> 00:31:35,648
That's why no one knows.

399
00:31:35,728 --> 00:31:36,898
Secretly?

400
00:31:38,478 --> 00:31:39,608
Why secretly?

401
00:31:39,688 --> 00:31:41,698
Because people gossip too much
about office romances.

402
00:31:41,778 --> 00:31:43,908
Besides, the employees will feel
very uncomfortable.

403
00:31:45,988 --> 00:31:46,988
I see.

404
00:31:52,578 --> 00:31:56,668
You still can't believe the fact
that I'm your fiancée?

405
00:31:59,088 --> 00:31:59,918
No.

406
00:32:06,298 --> 00:32:08,768
Then I should tell you how we met.

407
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:14,058
We met a year ago
when I was pointed as your secretary.

408
00:32:15,938 --> 00:32:18,398
You were a very nasty boss.

409
00:32:21,858 --> 00:32:23,148
You tormented your secretaries

410
00:32:23,238 --> 00:32:25,318
that none of them
lasted more than three months.

411
00:32:25,698 --> 00:32:28,698
I tormented my secretaries?

412
00:32:28,788 --> 00:32:31,748
Yes. It was so hard for me too.

413
00:32:31,828 --> 00:32:33,748
You threw sandwiches at me
and insulted me.

414
00:32:33,828 --> 00:32:35,288
It was a living hell!

415
00:32:39,338 --> 00:32:40,458
But, one day…

416
00:32:41,668 --> 00:32:43,008
you confessed

417
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:45,298
that you have feelings for me.

418
00:32:49,258 --> 00:32:51,678
I confessed?
Suddenly after tormenting you?

419
00:32:53,888 --> 00:32:57,438
Because you loved me so much.

420
00:32:58,438 --> 00:32:59,648
Basically,

421
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:02,108
you were crazy about me.

422
00:33:04,988 --> 00:33:06,238
Are you crazy?

423
00:33:06,318 --> 00:33:08,618
How could I say something so horrific?

424
00:33:08,698 --> 00:33:10,578
What? Acting isn't easy.

425
00:33:11,238 --> 00:33:14,828
You have to pour your heart
and soul into it

426
00:33:15,328 --> 00:33:17,998
-as much as you can.
-Jeez.

427
00:33:18,628 --> 00:33:20,338
I rejected you at first.

428
00:33:21,208 --> 00:33:23,588
But you cried and begged
saying you couldn't live without me

429
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:25,838
and threatened to kill yourself
unless I accepted you.

430
00:33:26,428 --> 00:33:28,008
-No, please marry me!
-Let go.

431
00:33:28,088 --> 00:33:29,258
Please marry me!

432
00:33:29,348 --> 00:33:31,138
No, I'm going to kill myself!

433
00:33:31,218 --> 00:33:32,468
Please marry me!

434
00:33:32,558 --> 00:33:35,268
I… begged you?

435
00:33:35,348 --> 00:33:36,308
Yes.

436
00:33:37,398 --> 00:33:39,188
So I accepted you in the end.

437
00:33:39,858 --> 00:33:42,398
And we got engaged a month ago
at your vacation house

438
00:33:42,938 --> 00:33:44,488
here in Gangneung.

439
00:33:45,318 --> 00:33:47,108
We exchanged vows secretly.

440
00:33:48,568 --> 00:33:51,328
I was a bit sad to do it
without our families there,

441
00:33:51,908 --> 00:33:55,498
but I did so
trusting your passionate love for me.

442
00:33:58,668 --> 00:34:01,878
What? "Trusting your passionate love…"

443
00:34:02,958 --> 00:34:06,718
With the gaze full of love,
say his name like this.

444
00:34:08,798 --> 00:34:10,258
Oh, Gojin.

445
00:34:15,768 --> 00:34:18,308
Okay, fine. Let's say I do that.

446
00:34:18,978 --> 00:34:19,978
Will he believe me?

447
00:34:20,268 --> 00:34:21,688
Even if he lost his memories,

448
00:34:21,768 --> 00:34:24,358
I need at least one picture with him
for him to believe me.

449
00:34:25,108 --> 00:34:26,778
Yes, pictures.

450
00:34:27,698 --> 00:34:29,908
We can just create them.

451
00:34:42,788 --> 00:34:44,838
Wait, what was that just now?

452
00:34:51,838 --> 00:34:54,638
This is our engagement ring.

453
00:34:56,638 --> 00:34:58,558
If you can't even trust
our memories together,

454
00:34:59,518 --> 00:35:01,808
I have no other way to prove it to you.

455
00:35:03,858 --> 00:35:04,938
Doctor.

456
00:35:06,858 --> 00:35:08,818
There is nothing more I can do.

457
00:35:08,898 --> 00:35:11,278
What else can I do to prove my love?

458
00:35:21,368 --> 00:35:22,418
I'm sorry,

459
00:35:23,668 --> 00:35:24,838
but honestly,

460
00:35:26,168 --> 00:35:28,048
everything feels like a dream

461
00:35:28,758 --> 00:35:30,128
and not real.

462
00:35:30,378 --> 00:35:35,508
Most patients with amnesia
have difficulty accepting their reality.

463
00:35:36,308 --> 00:35:38,348
A woman who you don't know
says she's your fiancée.

464
00:35:38,888 --> 00:35:40,518
It's hard to accept that.

465
00:35:45,228 --> 00:35:46,898
I guess I have to tell him this after all.

466
00:35:48,568 --> 00:35:51,028
The police suspect me
to be the hit-and-run driver.

467
00:35:51,108 --> 00:35:53,408
Even though I'm the one
who saved your life,

468
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:55,778
they think I'm the culprit who hit you.

469
00:35:59,158 --> 00:36:01,368
But the circumstances are…

470
00:36:01,458 --> 00:36:03,368
Yes, I understand your point of view.

471
00:36:03,458 --> 00:36:05,838
I went to his vacation house
with a claw hammer.

472
00:36:05,918 --> 00:36:07,458
You have a reason to suspect me.

473
00:36:08,628 --> 00:36:11,878
On top of that,
Gojin and I had a big argument that night.

474
00:36:12,798 --> 00:36:14,928
Because Gojin…

475
00:36:23,268 --> 00:36:24,598
cheated on me!

476
00:36:27,228 --> 00:36:28,068
Honey.

477
00:36:29,028 --> 00:36:30,228
Why are we taking this picture?

478
00:36:31,188 --> 00:36:32,278
You don't need to know.

479
00:36:39,578 --> 00:36:41,868
He cheated on me
immediately after we got engaged.

480
00:36:42,408 --> 00:36:43,748
So I thought about breaking up,

481
00:36:43,828 --> 00:36:45,578
and couldn't even tell anyone about it

482
00:36:45,788 --> 00:36:46,998
including our families.

483
00:36:51,048 --> 00:36:53,218
I wish I were the real culprit.

484
00:36:55,628 --> 00:36:57,298
If I had just let it slide,

485
00:36:57,388 --> 00:36:59,508
this accident wouldn't have happened.

486
00:37:02,178 --> 00:37:03,178
Yes.

487
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:06,228
I'm worse than the culprit.

488
00:37:09,398 --> 00:37:11,068
-Please arrest me.
-What…

489
00:37:11,148 --> 00:37:12,608
It's all my fault…

490
00:37:14,528 --> 00:37:16,158
that Gojin got into the accident.

491
00:37:41,598 --> 00:37:44,558
I got goosebumps. I'm so good at acting.

492
00:37:44,638 --> 00:37:46,308
Gosh, I'm amazing.

493
00:37:47,228 --> 00:37:48,268
Wow.

494
00:37:50,018 --> 00:37:51,108
Hi, Okhee.

495
00:37:52,858 --> 00:37:53,728
How did it go?

496
00:37:53,818 --> 00:37:56,948
My master, you are a true actress.

497
00:37:57,028 --> 00:37:59,528
You taught me so well. Hey.

498
00:37:59,618 --> 00:38:01,948
I guarantee you'll make it
to Cannes one day.

499
00:38:02,488 --> 00:38:05,368
Wow, you should've seen
Mr. Noh Manners' face.

500
00:38:05,448 --> 00:38:07,958
His face turned bright red, all flustered.

501
00:38:11,628 --> 00:38:13,128
Oh, the dress.

502
00:38:23,888 --> 00:38:24,888
Gojin!

503
00:38:25,518 --> 00:38:27,018
What happened to you?

504
00:38:27,478 --> 00:38:28,478
My goodness. Your leg…

505
00:38:29,398 --> 00:38:30,348
Are you okay otherwise?

506
00:38:31,018 --> 00:38:32,768
Is everything else okay?

507
00:38:35,148 --> 00:38:36,688
Who are you?

508
00:38:39,858 --> 00:38:40,698
Jeez.

509
00:38:41,488 --> 00:38:42,828
I guess you're feeling all right.

510
00:38:42,908 --> 00:38:44,658
You're even joking around.

511
00:38:44,738 --> 00:38:47,578
Do you even know
how scared I was on my way over here?

512
00:38:47,658 --> 00:38:49,078
My hands are still shaking.

513
00:38:59,258 --> 00:39:02,388
Sorry. Who is he?

514
00:39:03,678 --> 00:39:04,758
Mr. Oh.

515
00:39:07,268 --> 00:39:08,228
Mr. Oh?

516
00:39:09,188 --> 00:39:14,148
I see. So he must be
the deputy CEO of Gotop Education.

517
00:39:15,318 --> 00:39:17,738
Why are you speaking formally to me
all of a sudden?

518
00:39:18,318 --> 00:39:21,528
Gojin, it's me. It's Segi.

519
00:39:22,278 --> 00:39:24,198
Am I older than you?

520
00:39:32,708 --> 00:39:34,038
Amnesia?

521
00:39:36,458 --> 00:39:37,458
Yes.

522
00:39:38,378 --> 00:39:39,548
So you're telling me

523
00:39:40,128 --> 00:39:41,338
that Mr. Noh…

524
00:39:46,718 --> 00:39:47,968
He can't remember anything?

525
00:39:48,968 --> 00:39:49,808
No.

526
00:39:51,138 --> 00:39:54,648
He can't even remember his own name.

527
00:39:55,688 --> 00:40:00,438
Ms. Lee, you're not asking me
to actually believe that, are you?

528
00:40:00,528 --> 00:40:02,488
How does that make sense?

529
00:40:02,568 --> 00:40:05,318
Noh Gojin is the top instructor in Korea.

530
00:40:05,448 --> 00:40:07,788
How is it possible
that he can't remember me

531
00:40:07,868 --> 00:40:09,448
who is closest to him or his own name?

532
00:40:11,618 --> 00:40:12,958
I'm sorry.

533
00:40:20,128 --> 00:40:21,418
CONSULTATION ROOM, DR. YOO JAEHO

534
00:40:21,508 --> 00:40:24,548
Mr. Noh Gojin lost all his memories.

535
00:40:26,138 --> 00:40:30,098
He'll never get his memories back?

536
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:34,228
No, it was all temporary
base on the patients

537
00:40:34,308 --> 00:40:36,308
-who had side effects from anesthesia.
-I see.

538
00:40:37,898 --> 00:40:40,398
Then what can we do

539
00:40:40,478 --> 00:40:42,568
to help him recover his memories faster?

540
00:40:42,738 --> 00:40:46,568
The only thing you can do now
is to keep stimulating his brain.

